    "Name": "Porcupine",
    "Details": "This version, designed for battlefield use in 3132 under Jeremy Stuart, focuses on the Porcupine's specialization in charging. The PRC-3N includes impact-resistant armor to withstand its own charges, a Null-Signature system and a laser anti-missile system to avoid fire before charging, and a MASC and supercharger combo to enhance speed. Space for this equipment is made through the use of a 180-rated XXL engine and the removal of all ranged weaponry. These changes resulted in an expensive combat 'Mech without ranged capabilities, which made had no sales by 3135.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Distracting</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 0.99</color></b>",
